    "created_at": "2026-03-19T00:00:00.000Z",
    "notes": "VIX mean reversion strategy \u2014 COUNTERINTUITIVE but powerful. Logic: (1) ONLY enters when VIX>=18 (fear spike). On these days, IV is inflated \u2014 you're selling expensive premium. (2) Uses wider 0.20 delta strikes because the underlying is already far from ATM. (3) Primary profit driver is IV crush, not theta \u2014 if VIX reverts from 20 back to 15, you make money even if spot barely moves. (4) Auto-exits when VIX < 15 AND 40% of premium decayed \u2014 IV crush trade complete. (5) Hard exit at VIX>=28 \u2014 if fear escalates further, cut losses. (6) Breakeven buffer tightened to 30pts \u2014 less room to breathe but forces discipline. This strategy COMPLEMENTS the DNSS_IMPROVED \u2014 run them together: DNSS handles normal days, VIX_MEAN_REV activates on event days."
  },
